{"id":"evil-eye","term":"Evil eye","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 23:6\">Prov. 23:6</a>), figuratively, the envious or covetous. (Comp. <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 15:9\">Deut. 15:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 20:15\">Matt. 20:15</a>.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Proverbs 23:6","Deuteronomy 15:9","Matthew 20:15"]}